Everything Proxmox..

                            Everything About Setting Up Proxmox W/Specialized Code & Steps For My Homelab Setup

                                                Login 
                                                  Username: root <- No Caps
                                                  Password: Master Password


    Supply's -
    		1.USB Thumb Drive ( 16 GB - 32 GB )
    		2.USB Installer ( Rufus )
    		3.Proxmox VE.ISO ( Proxmox VE )

  	Step 1.
        Find USB Thumb Drive For Proxmox VE ISO Install.
          Download USB Installer - https://rufus.ie
          Download And Run - Rufus
    Step 2.
        Open Rufus 
          Device = The Install Location - USB Thumb Drive 
          Click The Select Button And Select Your Download Of Proxmox VE
          Click Start
    Step 3.
        Install Proxmox " Check Note's "

    Step 4.
        Clear Up Drive Space
          Click On Datacenter And Go To Stoarage 
          Right Click And Delete local-lvm
    Step 5.
        Time For Some Code
          Click On The Device Name ( ***-**-**-**-** )
          Click On >_ Shell And ENTER The Fallowing
       Code:
          lvremove /dev/pve/data    (enter) y for Yes (enter)
          lvresize -l +100%FREE /dev/pve/root    (enter)
          resize2fs /dev/mapper/pve-root    (enter)
    Step 6.
        Update Proxmox
      Code:
          apt update && apt dist-upgrade    (enter)
    Step 7.
        Time To Remove That NO SUBSCRIPTION Pop Up
        **$**$$**$$$*$$**$** Work In Progress **$**$$**$$$**$$**$**
    Notes :

        Setup Password Use Master Password Its Going To Be Open To The Internet  ( Easy Password = Easy To Hack )
        Master Password Will Be Login Password..

        Make Sure You Use .local ( Example - ServerName.local ) ( **-**-**-**-**.local )
        NOTE!!! - Server Name = Name Of Server On Network & Device Name
